b'[<p><i><b>UFC 136: Edgar vs. Maynard III</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on October 8, 2011, at the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Toyota_Center_(Houston)" title="Toyota Center (Houston)">Toyota Center</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Houston,_Texas" title="Houston, Texas">Houston, Texas</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFC_136_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFC_136-3">[3]</a></sup> The event coincided with a two-day UFC Fan Expo held at the <a href="/wiki/George_R._Brown_Convention_Center" title="George R. Brown Convention Center">George R. Brown Convention Center</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><i>UFC 136</i> featured two preliminary fights live on <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Spike_TV" title="Spike TV">Spike TV</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-Spike_7-0"><a href="#cite_note-Spike-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Josh_Grispi" title="Josh Grispi">Josh Grispi</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Matt_Grice" title="Matt Grice">Matt Grice</a> at the event,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup> but Grispi was forced off the card with an injury and replaced by <a href="/wiki/Nam_Phan" title="Nam Phan">Nam Phan</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-GricePhan_9-0"><a href="#cite_note-GricePhan-9">[9]</a></sup> Grice himself was also forced from the card with an undisclosed injury and replaced by <a href="/wiki/Leonard_Garcia" title="Leonard Garcia">Leonard Garcia</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Aaron_Simpson_(fighter)" title="Aaron Simpson (fighter)">Aaron Simpson</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Nick_Catone" title="Nick Catone">Nick Catone</a> at the event but Catone was forced off the card with an injury and replaced by <a href="/wiki/Eric_Schafer" title="Eric Schafer">Eric Schafer</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SimpsonSchafer_11-0"><a href="#cite_note-SimpsonSchafer-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Mike_Russow" title="Mike Russow">Mike Russow</a> was scheduled to fight <a href="/wiki/Dave_Herman_(fighter)" title="Dave Herman (fighter)">Dave Herman</a> at the event, but the bout was cancelled after Herman failed his preliminary drug test in which he tested positive for <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Marijuana" title="Marijuana">marijuana</a>. Herman denies using the prohibited substance.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>This event held the UFC record for most time spent in actual fighting at 158 minutes and 32 seconds, beating the last record holder <i><a href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night:_Maynard_vs._Diaz" title="UFC Fight Night: Maynard vs. Diaz">UFC Fight Night: Maynard vs. Diaz</a></i>, which was 149 minutes and 50 seconds.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night:_Werdum_vs._Tybura" title="UFC Fight Night: Werdum vs. Tybura">UFC Fight Night: Werdum vs. Tybura</a></i> would later break this record on November 19, 2017, with a total of 184 minutes and 18 seconds of cage time.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Fighters were awarded $75,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-19"><a href="#cite_note-19">[15]</a></sup>\n</p>]'